Author: 2018，希望更好
Subject: 2018，希望更好
Body:
年，
就这样，
隆重而来，
悄然而去。
一年又一年，
丰富了记忆，苍老了容颜；
迎来了春光，送走了冬寒。
一年又一年，
期盼中载满祝福，
愿望中满是平安。
一年又一年，
从孩童走进中年，
从中年走进老年，
从丰满走向骨感。
一年又一年，
不必感慨也不必抱怨，
最好的皆是顺其自然。
一年又一年，
感恩生活也珍惜遇见，
执着努力亦随遇而安！

Author: 夸奖
Subject: 评论？能用？
Body:
谷歌地图是 Google 公司提供的电子地图服务，包括局部详细的卫星照片。此款服务可以提供含有政区和交通以及商业信息的矢量地图、不同分辨率的卫星照片和可以用来显示地形和等高线地形视图。
在2014年3月5日谷歌表示印度22个城市的用户已经可以访问谷歌地图中75个在当地比较流行的室内场地地图，包括位于古尔冈的Ambience Mall，以及德里的Select City Walk购物中心等。
Translated Body: Google Maps is an electronic map service provided by Google that includes locally detailed satellite photos. This service provides vector maps with political and traffic and business information, satellite photos of different resolutions, and terrain and terrain views that can be used to display topography and contour lines. On March 5, 2014, Google said users in 22 cities across India have been able to access 75 of the more popular indoor venues on Google Maps, including Ambience Mall in Gurgaon and Select City Walk in Delhi. .

Translated Body: In 2008, Wang mainland participated in the suspense drama "Perak MIT", as an actor debut [1]. In 2009, he starred in the family drama "shiny day." In 2010, he starred in thriller drama "National Heroes" [2]. In 2015, Wang was well-known to the audience for playing the role of actor Xu Taoyu in his youth school movie My Girlhood, which became the 2015 box office champion of the year in Taiwan. After the release of the Chinese mainland, the box office exceeded 300 million yuan [3] . In November 2016, Wang continent starred in the love movie "28-year-old underage" [4]; in December, he co-starred with Jackie Chan in the action comedy movie "Flying Tiger" [5]. Author: Raym no2
Subject: Ouch They killed it
Body:
Update! 2/18/17 After the updating to 4.45 I find Google killed a great app. I have an IPhone and even after reloading it a couple of times the update has made the app worthless.
1. The path is no longer “track up” and the path is heading to the bottom of the screen.
2. The screen freezes and the icon representing your location is always miles behind your actual location.
3. Sometimes the icon representing your location simply reverses and runs backwards?
4. At any given time the Icon representing your location will just float off of the programmed part.
5. Sometimes the sound announces the directions but more often than not there is no sound. 
There is just too much more to write in a review column! Did anyone at google even test this? Google is usually so dependable and so good with its programs.........what happened here.
Do not update!!! I only hope someone does not get into b=a bad situation due to the latest update!

I think the title tells it all. Lacking is the ability to get longitude and latitude for when driving in the country, and setting parking locations quickly. Finally, some of the best features are not as intuitive as some other offerings but it is usually in there some place. But, there are some neat features you cannot find in other packages. Best of all it gives you choices of routes and has never given bad directions or left me stranded. And google is improving the software all the time. Of the three packages I have in my phone this is my go to navigation app.

Author: Sylett
Subject: Latest update broke routing options
Body:
As a driving instructor I often change the routing options to avoid motorways for learners and to allow them for myself. 

In previous versions when the route was displayed on the screen there were three dots you could click to change the route options. It would offer you an option to “remember settings” meaning if I was just setting up a one time route for a learner driver I could untick this option and the next time I opened the app it would auto route on the motorway. 

In this version the settings have moved, no longer have a remember settings option and completely don’t work at all. I set the sat nav up after selecting avoid motorways and it tried sending a learner driver onto the m1. I tried again, same result. 

With the sat nav addition to the driving test this is unacceptable.

Author: MU-555
Subject: WORSENED consistently after each update!!
Body: This is one app that actually got WORSE after every update. Some good features removed, other new features that aren't very practical added in. But aside from that it's been very buggy, crashes, layout is extremely poor, usability is also extremely poor! Constant updates and revamps and tweaks making it inconsistent. Functionality and form thrown out the window. Street view is an embarrassment and not accurate. The 1 star rating is given only because on some occasions, it does get me from A to B. Rerouting is now just messed up, estimation time and the direction of the arrow is laughable. Before you can use this app without having to specifically navigate somewhere- you can roam around and your maps will follow regardless - why was this feature removed?? Sometimes I need to know the surrounding places for parking or locating other stuff! Free roaming was one of the reason why I used GMaps over TomTom which does allow free roaming but not as good. And lastly, does offline mode actually work?!! I've downloaded all relevant maps and would use the phone on airplane mode, get it forces me to connect to mobile data?! Still struggle why this app uses data rather than GPS. Just overall poor hate it now!

Author: Scimom
Subject: No speed limit, no cameras = useless
Body: I just deleted the app after using it for almost a year. It makes it impossible to submit feedback while on the road, so few people submit updates. It is really behind on changes. Most importantly, a navigation without a speed limit info and an alert if speeding, is useless. Of course, no speed camera alert either. Don’t use this app if you go to Germany, there are hundreds of hidden speed reductions, followed by a camera. The speed change is not visible, you need an alert. Using this app almost guarantees getting trapped by these.

Author: iPhonePhive
Subject: Offline maps expire every 29 days! Why?
Body: I don't understand why offline maps expire at all, nevermind in 29 days! After 29 days you can no longer use the offline maps unless you update them. Do the world's roads suddenly disappear? Google seems to think it's better to leave you stranded without any offline maps than to leave you with slightly out dated offline maps. Outdated being 29 days of course. I'm pretty sure not much happens to roads in 29 days..... This is a problem because Google seems to want to update them about every 14 days or before they expire. You have to leave the app open while they update. If you close the app during an update, or are off WiFi, your offline maps won't work. Unfortunately for me this caused me to leave for a trip when offline maps had not finished updating. Rendering Google maps useless to me when I had no cell signal. For a group of intelligent people this is surely very dumb. Let us use outdated maps if we need to. Otherwise Google maps is considered unreliable.

Author: Анараперо
Subject: Сароллор
Body:
В целом о работе приложения знают все. Хочу лишь акцентировать внимание на одной детали, которая порядком выбешивает. Крик души!!!

В городе, не имея компаса под рукой, и так сложно найти эти стороны света, а тем более сориентироваться, едучи в машине в интенсивном дорожном трафике.
Translated Body: In general, everyone knows about the work of the application. I just want to focus on one detail, which flies out in order. Cry from the heart!!! So you want to call the developers of navigation full of idiots and idiots, when the navigator once again in a nice voice tells you to turn to the north-east or south-west. In a city without a compass at hand, it's so difficult to find these parts of the world, let alone navigate, riding in a car in heavy traffic.

Author: Behind the curtain
Subject: Destination arrived is terrible
Body: Navigation stops and the map orients north when you are nearby rather than actually arrived. This often means navigation stops in areas with dense roads (estates) or when approaching from behind or the side (e.g. approaching road passes behind the destination). Reorienting north at arrival is confusing since map orientation suddenly swivels away from the navigation perspective and you need to mentally reorient the map to get your bearings at an unfamiliar location.

Author: MIKE111999333
Subject: 评论可以用吗？
Body: 其实我知道评论了也不能用，因为没有这样的接口判断你是否评论。但我还是一直渴望可以用上谷歌地图，记得零几年还没有3g网络的时候，我用诺基亚的2g谷歌地图，去了好多好多地方，准确、可靠，规划路线时会合理安排可以选择的公共交通。一几年的时候，我用腾讯地图在上海，推荐我坐2号线还是几号线来着去目的地，到了换乘站，被告知今晚已经停运。大晚上我感到无比迷茫，走了老远才拦到一辆愿意从浦东去浦西的出租车。这些在谷歌都是不会发生的，它会告诉你这条线已停运。现在谷歌地图被和谐了，我并不感到愤怒，只是感到有点可惜。可能这是上层敏感保守的一种保护选择，这是我所接触不到的层面。作为一个平凡人从内心我不支持这样，我只是希望尽早有一天能再次开放，我希望早日可以用上它！
Translated Body: In fact, I know the comments can not be used, because there is no such interface to judge whether you comment. But I still have long been eager to use Google Maps, I remember a few years there is no 3g network, I use Nokia's 2g Google maps, went to many places, accurate and reliable, planning routes will be able to reasonably arrange the public can choose traffic. A few years, I use Tencent map in Shanghai, I recommend line 2 or a few lines to the destination, to the transfer station, was told tonight has been suspended. Big night I feel very confused, walked all the way stopped to a willing to go from Pudong to Puxi taxi. These do not happen on Google, it will tell you that this line is out of service. Google Maps is now harmonious, I am not angry, just feel a pity. Maybe this is a protection option that the upper-level is sensitive and conservative, which is beyond my reach. As an ordinary person from the heart I do not support this, I just hope that one day as soon as possible to open again, I hope it can be used as soon as possible!

Author: phantomtails
Subject: What happened?
Body:
Google Maps used to be the gold standard, such that I wouldn’t go near Apple Maps even when it began to improve. However, the quality of the navigation has deteriorated significantly recently. I’ve seen it consistently announce turns late, prematurely, or not at all; continuously adjust my location; and not provide timely lane guidance. In addition, the traffic information is often unreliable — it
often shows traffic jams that have long since cleared up, and I’ve found that Apple Maps is more reliable at displaying short-term road closures.

I still have trust problems with Apple Maps, but Google is forcing my hand because I cannot use an app that causes me to miss turns due to poor timing of announcements.

I was going down the highway and all the sudden it just told me to take a turn I reacted in an hour later I arrived at my first stop. Author: Future NowHere
Subject: Great for info on businesses and fast directionally
Body:
I used to use it solely. Even help w the beta versions.

Here are things that i would like to see:

1. Night mode on all screens including search.
2. A minimal setting w large icons on a mostly black and white/ greyscale.
3. Recentering that isn’t a tiny button on bottom left, or auto recentering after a certain time setting. Or just touch the middle anywhere to recenter. Or a no recentering altogether setting.
4. Speed limit/ mph setting.
5. Quick setting for parks and things other then eating and consuming.
6. Three next turns, so as to avoid crossing lanes of traffic hastily. 
7. Not so many road names that clog up map. Just major ones.
8. Notifications that aren’t blinding 
9. Automatic go instead of so many taps
10. When searching for a place, the miles and time end up being longer on start. Sometimes drastically.
11. No blue or green except for parks.
12. Specific favorite store markers that don’t have to be put in individually. As well as a favorite searches easy access.
13. Electric car charge points.
14. Gestures w multi finger taps and swipes and long presses.
15. Suggestions for sights along the way related to interests and interesting facts.
16. Ability to download larger areas.
17. Venue schedules and times and tickets.
18. Popular places at the moment for different events. Or future events to participate in, along w easy way to add to calendar and pay w phone.
19. Option for the most chill back routes for people not in a rush.
20. Lists of natural places to go to for quiet meditation/ mental health.
21. Ability to put in mpg and tank size of car/ type of vehicle make model, so it can track and analyze driving.
22. Suggestions to take a break/ nap.
23. Positive affirmations/ road facts and knowledge to curb road rage/ ease stress, like how having lots of distance from the car in front of you prevents almost all accidents and traffic. Along w driving the speed limit and enjoying the ride. Enjoying driving again. Enjoying life in general.

I really like that it shows things about different neighborhoods. It could go into more detail about this. Maybe show history of places and more things to do for all types of people.

Author: amw01
Subject: Transit features are key
Body:
I use Google Maps almost daily - it’s often faster and more direct to find out when the next bus/train is coming through Google Maps than it is through the Metro app or website. 

There is still room for improvement though. First, I’m not crazy about the new update that shows when nearby routes arrive. For people who only need to take one bus or train to get to their destination, I can absolutely see how this is a great feature, but if you’re like me and you need to make at least one transfer, it’s not really very helpful and it now inevitably takes me longer each time I open the app to go if the next route to where I’m going. Second, for transit directions, I would love to be able to select routes based on how little time I have to spend waiting for a transfer. I would almost always rather take a route that was 10 minutes longer in total if it means I don’t have to spend as long waiting at the stop between buses. I live in a place that can regularly be over 100 degrees in the summer - don’t want to wait outside in that heat - and then cold/windy/rainy in the winter - and dark, and I don’t want to wait in that either. If there was a way to take that into account, or at least make it more obvious how long the transfer time is for various routes, I would love that. 

Finally, I’ve noticed when people put my home into the GPS, it had them turn down a street that I don’t live on. I’m somewhat near the intersection with that street, but not even on the corner. It would be great to be able to adjust within the map how an address is displayed/a pin dropped. 

Thanks for always working hard to improve your products.

A small suggestion to the development team: Please make it possible to specify intermediate goals, so that you can determine a certain route from the outset. Body: Es gibt zwei Mängel:  1.) Fehlerhafte Karten (Beispiel Mannheim). Es kommt vor, dass ganze Hausnummern verkehrt herum sind, sprich man will eigentlich an das eine Ende der Straße, aber wird ans andere navigiert (Beispiel: Speckweg Mannheim). Dann kommt es vor, dass die App einen manchmal VERKEHRT durch Einbahnstraßen fahren lassen will (Stadtteil Sandhofen in Mannheim)! Das schlimmste ist aber in den Quadraten von Mannheim, was ein Labyrinth ist und man meistens auf eine Navigation angewiesen ist, man wird zwar zum richtigen Quadrat navigieren, aber häufig zu einer x-beliebigen Hausnummer, aber nicht zur richtigen!  2.) Die Hausnummerneingabe. Wenn ich zu einen späteren Zeitpunkt eine Hausnummer eingeben möchte, dann will ich nicht in der einen Zeile herumspielen bis ich die richtige Stelle erwicht habe. Bitte ein zusätzliches Feld dafür.
Translated Body: There are two deficiencies: 1.) Defective maps (example Mannheim). It happens that whole house numbers are upside down, that means one actually wants to reach one end of the street, but is navigated to the other one (example: Speckweg Mannheim). Then it happens that the app wants to drive a sometimes TRAFFIC by one-way streets (district Sandhofen in Mannheim)! The worst thing is in the squares of Mannheim, which is a labyrinth and you usually rely on navigation, you will indeed navigate to the correct square, but often to a x-any house number, but not the right one! 2.) The house number input. If I want to enter a house number at a later date, I do not want to play around in the one line until I reach the right spot. Please add an additional field.

Eigentlich hilft sie nur bei der Suche nach S-Bahn Verbindungen, für alles andere nutze ich die Öffi App! Local Guides ist jetzt allerdings auch nach Google Maps umgezogen, und dafür benötigt man die App nun mal zwingend.
Translated Body: In the search for streets and addresses good and indispensable. This means that I use Google Maps like a city map - but as a navigation for the bus and train traffic, this app is completely unsuitable here. Actually, it helps only in the search for S-Bahn connections, for everything else I use the Öffi App! However, Local Guides has now moved to Google Maps too, and for that you need the app.

Author: Гаврил Астафьев
Body: Началось с того что я начал писать отзывы о различных местах посещённых мною, было прикольно. Однажды Гугл попросил меня написать отзыв о кафе в котором я не был, я поставил что я там не был, на следующий день ситуация повторилась, я снова сообщил Гуглу что меня там не было, после двух недельных домогательств я написал в Гугл саппорт с просьбой о том чтобы меня не донимали этим кафе, потому что я там никогда не был и не планирую там побывать. Со временем число таких мест где Гугл считает что я был, увеличилось. Устал от этих уведомлений, пропало желание оставлять отзывы о тех местах где я был.
Translated Body: It started with the fact that I started writing reviews about the various places visited by me, it was fun. Once Google asked me to write a review about a cafe in which I was not, I said that I was not there, the next day the situation repeated, I again told Google that I was not there, after two weeks of harassment, I wrote to Google support asking for that I was not pestered by this cafe, because I was never there and do not plan to visit there. Over time, the number of such places where Google believes that I was, has increased. Tired of these notifications, the desire to leave feedback about the places where I was was lost.

Author: Naomi Rose
Body: I usually avoid using this app until the last minute. I travel a lot for work and I've found that even though it claims to provide you with the best routes, you usually extend the time of your trip by several minutes, if you follow their routes from beginning to end. It gives traffic updates but not beforehand. So, by the time you are alerted, you're already smack dead into the hazard. You can save your home and work address and download offline maps for when you're in areas with spotty coverage, which can be helpful. Overall, is OK but can definitely be improved.

In passato era possibile inviare al telefono un percorso, spero venga ripristinata questa funzione. Talvolta, inoltre, il navigatore mi ha fatto girare tondo a vuoto senza motivo apparente. Funzionava meglio prima.
Translated Body: It does not allow navigation with routes already set on web browsers, or in stages. The route chosen by the navigator is forced, not taking into account some variables. In the past it was possible to send a route to the phone, I hope this function is restored. In addition, sometimes, the navigator made me turn round without any apparent reason. It worked better before.

Author: Josef Nožka
Body: ....všem co nechtějí offline navi, ale zde stále nadávají na Hlavní.mapy, doporučuji konkurenční app. mapy.cz. Získáte super kvalitní turistické mapy (ty lze i postahovat a na SD  uložit!!!), ok vyhledání,  hlavně pak navi v autě (pouze osobním a jen 2D), ale i cyklo, pěší i v terénu. Lze si trasu postavit z libovolného počtu PB...atd, zkuste, uvidíte. A teď jsem zvědav, do kdy tady tohle Google ponechá, než to smázne. Ale jelikož zde absolutně na nic nereagují, tak uvidíme zda s nimi alespoň tohle nějak pohne....
Translated Body: .... all those who do not want to go offline, but they are still dancing on MainMaps, I recommend a competitive app. mapa.cz. You get top quality maps (you can also catch up and save the SD !!!), ok search, especially in the car (only personal and only 2D), but also cycling, walking and outdoors. You can build a route from any number of PB ... etc, try, you will see. And now I'm wondering how long this Google will leave it until it clears up. But as they do not react absolutely to anything here, we'll see if they move at least somehow.

Author: Dana Gibboney
Body: Maps has worked nicely for me for years. My only gripe is that Google doesn't post a detailed changelog or "what's new" with the updates, and therefore I'm hesitant to apply them.  Years of bad experiences have taught me that I need to carefully weigh the risk/reward when deciding whether to update stable apps, and it's a pain to have to read through a bunch of reviews to try to figure out what the changes even are, then whether all of the complaints are valid or just the rantings of the clueless.  So, I'm a few updates behind, wondering if I'm missing out on a better experience, but overall pretty satisfied. 4 stars from me.

Author: Arenda 161
Body: Самый лучший навигатор из за его универсальности для всех типов передвижения! Все в одном месте. Не нужно как в яндексе: один навигатор для авто; другой для пешеходов и общественного транспорта; и нет описания обьектов. По мексике проехали 3700 км прекрасно по этому навигатору. В европе прекрасно помогает передвигаться хоть на ковре  самолете! И автоматически включается геолокация! В общем функционален и практичен в использовании.

Author: RARA AVIS
Body: Лаги автоматом після відключення геоданих. Варінти: 1 - Гугл спеціально вмикає "режим лагів" для того, щоб заставити увімкнути геодані. 2 - Код прописаний так, що будь-яка дія йде через пошук геоданих. Який би варіант не був, Гугл займаються вичисленням переміщень усіх власників Андроїд. Не дивно чому викинули старі додатки з магазину, щоб примусово заставити користуватись смартіонами, які можна відстежувати.
Translated Body: Logs by auto-off after turning off location. Varietti: 1 - Google specially activates the "mode of logs" in order to force turning on location. 2 - The code is written so that any action goes through the search of location data. Whatever the option, Google is engaged in calculating the displacements of all Android owners. It is not surprising why they threw out old apps from the store to force them to use obsessed marathons that can be tracked.

Habe diese app heute das erste mal probiert, weil mein richtiges navi dessen name ich nicht erwähne, einen miserablen content manager hat (wollte nur die karte aktualisieren) und brauchte daher eine alternative. Ich muss sagen, das diese app sehr gut arbeitet aber offenbar nur, wenn ich in bestimmten Bereichen netz hab (ist nichts tragisches, verfahren hab ich nicht), ich wurde sehr zuverlässig geführt und habe mein ziel problemlos erreicht. Danke dafür :)

Author: Olaf Schmidt
Body: Gerade in Hinblick auf die aktuelle Verkehrslage ist Google Maps unübertroffen. Wie die Daten dafür zusammengetragen werden, möchte man sich lieber nicht vorstellen - komplette Bewegungsprofile der Nutzer sind da jedenfalls ein nettes 'Abfallprodukt'.  Die Möglichkeit der direkten Suche von Restaurants oder anderen Anlaufstellen klappt (auch per Spracheingabe) dank der Verbindung mit der Google-Suche sehr gut. Die Navigation ist ordentlich und wird sogar verbessert, wenn man sich verfahren und dies zurückgemeldet hat.  Die Möglichkeit des Herunterladens von Offline-Karten hat es ermöglicht, dass Google Maps in Verbindung mit Android Auto mein Navi im Fahrzeug komplett ersetzt hat.

Кстати, о нехоженных лесах. Было бы здорово, что бы дорога выбиралась не только с учётом расстояния, но и с учётом того, какая она, 800 км без заправок и кафе, это тяжеловато...

Body: 【追記:最新版に更新後、タイムラインで実際に行った場所の近くで行ってない場所が経由地に登録されてしまい削除しても何度も復活してしまうようになりました。修正お願いします。】2018年になってアップデートをしてから、過去のタイムラインの一部で店舗名表記だったはずのところが町名表記になってしまった箇所がいくつもあり困る。あと、スマホの設定で、Smart Lockで信頼できる場所の設定をしているのですが、最近、その場所でしばらくスマホを使わないでいるとロックがかかってしまい、この症状が出るようになったのもGoogleマップのアプデ後からの気がします。タイムラインの一番上の日付が途切れるようになりました。「2017年10月9日」はちゃんと表示されるのですが、月と日のどちらも2桁になると「2017年10月1…」と表示されてしまいます。とても見にくいので修正をお願いしたいです。それと経由地の並び替えがあると便利。

Author: A Google User
Body: I've been using this for a year and a bit now for my job.   It keeps having stupid things added or changed that dont need adding or changing.  First, why is it now turning the traffic on whenever I start the app? I have traffic turned off, its too much clutter. Previously it left traffic off if I had it on. Why would you remove the fumctionality of remembering previous settings? Its stupid. Let me keep traffic off.  Secondly, when typing in an address, if its a unit based address, say 1/50 Road name, as in number 50, unit 1, it will switch it around and send me to 50/1. As in number 1, unit 50. Why? It didnt use to do this. Of course, if I try to type in 50/1 it doesnt switch that around to give me what I want. Its so infuritating.  Next, sometimes, ill type 50a name road. It will bring up an extra menu. "Did you mean 50a, or 50b" which takes 3 extra clicks to get through to start the route. I typed 50a. You would think I meant 50a google!  Next, I type 50 name road. So what does it do sometimes? Completely ignore the "50" and give me just the road, taking me to the middle the road. Which is all well and good until I wanted an address on a very long road, and it took me to an arbitary point on that road 15 minutes away from the address on that road I physically specified.   The actual address is important, because I use the app most of the time to find the exact location of the address I want on the road, so im not trundlinf down it at low speed trying to squint at letterboxes. So all of these issues are quite annoying for me.    Oh, also, sometimes it will randomly try to route me around one specific stretch of road. It once tried its level best to route me around one 200m stretch of road between two intersections, including giving me a 10 minute detour at one point, for no reason. I ignored it and drove down the road.  Also, sometimes it'll get the address right, then randomly place the route to end somewhere nowhere near that address. Sometimes not even on the same road. Or a road near where the address is.

Author: Miles Conlan
Body: Good overall, but a handful of complains as it relates to its implementation on Android Auto.  The single worst offence is how it must announce details of the trip before giving directions. I can't tell you how many times I have missed a turn because it *needs* to tell me that traffic is light. Why can't we seem to set routes to always avoid tolls/gravel/etc, and is there no way to toggle those options within Android Auto? Why can't we hide or minimize the card that's on the left if we're navigating? There are a number of missing features that make me either pull over and use my phone, or just give up altogether, and that's not good.

Author: MrPoliedrus
Body: Lo sto usando da un mesetto e lo trovo utile e piacevole. Funziona discretamente e le indicazioni sono abbastanza  precise e tempestive. Le segnalazioni delle camere semaforo e/o autovelox mobili sono un po' lenti, ma considerando che è gratis e senza pubblicità  va benone. Login a creazione account macchinoso, ho dovuto crearne uno nuovo,  il primo non funzionava.
Translated Body: I'm using it for a month and I find it useful and enjoyable. It works discreetly and the directions are quite precise and timely. The signals of the traffic lights and / or mobile cameras are a bit 'slow, but considering that it is free and without advertising is fine. Login to creating a cumbersome account, I had to create a new one, the first one did not work.

App Name: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Body: Ich habe sie zunächst auf einer mir sehr gut bekannten Strecke ausprobiert und mehrmals versucht, eine schon seit zwei Wochen vorhandene Baustelle mit Ampel zu melden, was aber nie gespeichert wurde. Die Baustelle ist immer noch da, aber in der App taucht sie nicht auf! Staus zeigt sie auch nicht immer an (im Gegensatz zu Google-Maps) und sie leitete mich auf eine Strecke mit 400 Meter Umweg (unnötigerweise). Also, ich bin nicht wirklich begeistert...
Translated Body: I first tried it on a very well-known track and tried several times to report a two-week-old construction site with traffic lights, but this was never saved. The construction site is still there, but it does not show up in the app! It also does not always indicate traffic jams (unlike Google maps) and it steered me to a 400-meter detour (unnecessarily). Well, I'm not really excited ...

Author: Evgeny Vladimirovich
Body: Перешел на Васю чуть более чем пол года назад. Очень доволен. Дизайн и интерфейс радуют. Нравится, что можно оперативно сообщить о каком либо дорожном событии или погодных условиях, но есть ощущение, что пользователей мало, т.е. социальная составляющая проекта недостаточна. Надеюсь мои отчеты приносят кому-то пользу. Однако по стандартному маршруту из дома на работу через день вынужден ставить знак выбоин на одном и том же месте, на след. день они опять пропадают. Разработчики думают, что выбоины на дороге ремонтируются в течении суток сами?
Translated Body: He switched to Vasya just over half a year ago. Very satisfied. The design and the interface are encouraging. I like that you can quickly report on a road event or weather conditions, but there is a feeling that there are few users, i.e. the social component of the project is insufficient. I hope my reports bring someone benefits. However, the standard route from home to work every other day is forced to put a sign potholes in the same place on the trail. day they again disappear. Do the developers think that the potholes on the road are repaired within 24 hours?

Author: Dany Caballero
Body: Bajé de 5 a una estrella, por qué? Simple: deben entender como es México, No es como otro países, donde si una calle está cerrada por obras, al otro día está abierta. Aquí pueden pasar 3 años antes de que acaben y abran el camino, es bastante incómodo que diario me mande por una calle cerrada, que diario yo tenga que poner  que no se puede pasar, y al otro día me vuelva a mandar por ahí y tenga que volver a poner que está cerrada.
Translated Body: I went down from 5 to a star, why? Simple: they must understand how is Mexico, It is not like other countries, where if a street is closed for works, the next day is open. Here it may be 3 years before they finish and open the way, it is quite uncomfortable that daily send me down a closed street, that every day I have to put that can not be passed, and the next day I send again and have They put it back closed.

Author: Advocacia Cabral
Body: Depois da última atualização melhorou. Tem um pequeno atraso de localização. As vezes informa para entrar na via mas já passou. Tem que ficar atendo quando ele informa a distância para a alteração de via, diminuir bem a velocidade para não errar a entrada. Quando fica buscando sinal, é só desligar e ligar o sinal de GPS que ele volta a funcionar corretamente.
Translated Body: After the last update it improved. There is a little delay in locating. Sometimes it tells you to get in the way but it's over. You have to keep an eye on him when he informs the distance to the change of way, slow down well not to miss the entrance. When you are searching for a signal, just turn the GPS signal off and on and it will work correctly again.

Body: Хороший навигатор. Интерфейс гораздо удобнее,чем в 2 гис. Показывает где повернуть, где светофоры. Карта удобнее,чем в других приложениях и местоположение определяет точнее. Можно проложить нужный маршрут и следовать по нему. Также в приложении отображаются городские достопримечательности, что значительно облегчает путешествие. В общем, рекомендую устанавливать и пользоваться.
Translated Body: Good navigator. The interface is much more convenient than in 2 gigs. Shows where to turn, where traffic lights. The map is more convenient than in other applications and the location determines more accurately. You can build the desired route and follow it. Also, the application displays city attractions, which greatly facilitates the journey. In general, I recommend to install and use.

Author: Alejandro Muñoz
Body: Aun hay muchas cosas por mejorar, me ha tocado desinstalarlo porque activo la ruta y de un momento a otro se queda parado y se sale de la app, apagando la ruta, además, si hay atascos, accidentes, trafico parado te sigue guiando por la ruta sin sacarte de esos atascos, aveces es como si uno le activara alguna opción de "enviarme por la vía más congestionada" porque a pesar de trancones no te saca por rutas alternas, por otro lado, se demore bastante en decirnos las indicaciones, muchas veces cuando vamos a mas de 80km/h te da la orden de girar ya cuando estas encima del giro.
Translated Body: There are still many things to improve, I had to uninstall it because I activate the route and from one moment to another it is stopped and leaves the app, turning off the route, also, if there are traffic jams, accidents, stopped traffic, it continues guiding you through the route without getting out of those traffic jams, sometimes it is as if one activates some option to "send me by the most congested route" because in spite of traffic jams it does not take you out on alternate routes, on the other hand, it takes a long time to tell us the indications, many Sometimes when we go over 80km / h, it gives you the order to turn already when you are on top of the turn.

Author: Demis Cunha
Body: O poder do social no GPS. Muito bom! Contudo, precisa melhorar o seguinte: 1 - Mapa Offline. Muitos pontos na estrada não tem sinal e fica impossível calcular novas rotas. Salvar rota offline é importante.  2 - Incluir pedágio. Incluir as praças, valores e mostrar o quanto vão ser gastos durante a viagem. 3 - Aprendizados. O App precisa aprender a rota mais utilizada. Ele calcula A mas sempre faço uma pequena diferença. Depois de algumas viagens ele deveria aprender e sugerir rotas frequentes. 4 - Compartilhar. Compartilhar rota em tempo real como o Google Maps faz. 5 - Amigos. Visualizar posição dos amigos no mapa em tempo real. 6 - Atalhos. Atalho multi touch para alguns alertas. Ex. tocar com 3 dedos na tela inclui alerta de radar na rota imediatamente.
Translated Body: The power of social in GPS. Very good! However, you need to improve the following: 1 - Offline Map. Many points on the road have no signal and it is impossible to calculate new routes. Saving offline route is important. 2 - Include toll. Include the squares, values ​​and show how much they will be spent while traveling. 3 - Learning. The App needs to learn the most commonly used route. He calculates A but always makes a small difference. After a few trips he should learn and suggest frequent routes. 4 - Share. Share real-time route as Google Maps does. 5 - Friends. View friends' position on the map in real time. 6 - Shortcuts. Multi touch shortcut for some alerts. Eg touching with 3 fingers on the screen includes radar alert on the route immediately.

App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Francis GALTIER
Body: Info pour les développeurs de Waze. Le model de calcul des temps de trajet ne prend pas assez en compte la situation du trafic en temps réel. Il utilise trop l’historique du trafic enregistré sur le trajet aux mêmes horaires. Pendant la période de vacances dans une région, les temps de trajets sont en écart par rapport à la réalité. Exemple : Le 19/02/2018 (période de vacances scolaire en Ile de France) pour un trajet de 33km temps indiqué 55mn avec un départ à 8h25. En réalité sur cet itinéraire le temps de trajet à été de 30mn. Une première mise à jour du temps s’est fait au bout de 6km avec un gain annoncé de 10mn puis au bout de 15km nouveau gain annoncé de 8mn et pour finir 4 km avant l’arrivé le vrai ETA s’affiche. Il devient difficile d’avoir confiance sur le ETA annoncé et sur le meilleur itinéraire à suivre.  En espérant une mise à jour pour revenir à 5 Etoiles, je passe la note à 2 Etoiles.

Author: js0
Body: I actually have very few complaints about Waze in general; I use it probably daily and am considered a top contributor in my area. However, the fact that I can't disable the automatic routing when I initially open the app pisses me off to absolutely no end. Not only do I rarely use Waze for navigation due to having a dedicated GPS unit, but that feature sometimes bogs down my phone if I'm in an area with limited network service and it wastes my time while causing unnecessary frustration!

App Name: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Jantzen Deppe
Body: I REALLY wanted to love this app. I have found some things about Google maps that I don't really like and this all promised to solve a lot of those. However, there are a ton of little glitchy things this app does that make it almost unbearable to use. For example...when a car is reported to be pulled over ahead on the shoulder the app says 'WATCH OUT. Vehicle stopped on shoulder ahead.' I about have a heart attack every time I'm driving and hear the announcement WATCH OUT and then it is simply to let me know some semi is four lanes away from me off on the shoulder. Another example is that turns aren't specified to help you find them - for instance on Google maps a 'slight left' is different than a 'left turn' to let you know how tight of a corner you'll be making. Tons and tons of small annoyances about the app add up to make it more of a hassle to use it than it is worth.

Author: Margot Barbelet
Body: J'utilisais très régulièrement Waze à ses débuts et en étais très satisfaite. Mais depuis plusieurs mois, l'application bugue régulièrement, a à chaque fois de grosses difficultés à me situer par exemple sur autoroute quand je croise d'autres voies (départementales...), n'arrive pas à recalculer le trajet ou ne trouve pas l'adresse même si j'ai un bon réseau. En vérifiant si cela ne venait pas de mon téléphone avec d'autres applications : aucun problème. Très déçue de ce changement...
Translated Body: I used Waze very early and was very satisfied. But for several months, the application bugue regularly, each time has great difficulties to find me for example on highway when I cross other roads (departmental ...), can not recalculate the route or found not the address even if I have a good network. By checking if it did not come from my phone with other applications: no problem. Very disappointed with this change ...

Author: Shinjiro Ushiama
Body: Pretty good as far as GPS goes but it would be nice to have the option of adding difficult junctions or turns either personally or through the map editor. Some junctions it suggests are just impractical. The most annoying thing about this app is how it guesses where you want to go when you open the app. Please allow us to turn this off as it is hardly ever right and unless you cancel it in time, it assumes that's where you want to go. Even on occassions where it is correct, I don't ever use the route it wants me to take because the junction it wants me to cross is across 6 lanes of traffic with no traffic lights.

App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Ken carter
Body: This app used to be great. Now it sends me and directions that are further away than routes that I know in a waste of time to use the app anymore. This morning they sent me down the road and caused me to get a ticket in an area where I wasn't very familiar with. That's the final straw for me so I'm deleting this app and going back to using Google Maps because it is at least a stable platform and consistent on how I send you to your point of destination. I use this app for wrecks and Hazards and warnings about police in the area and I really enjoyed using it when I first installed it but I have to say these latest versions are absolute garbage, not trustworthy or dependable in relation to its accuracy. I was five minutes from my destination this morning when I've got written up and after getting to where I needed to go, realized it took me in a complete circle, on a road that I didn't even need to be on.

App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Yarnsmith Amber
Body: The directions are insane, literally having me drive in circles. I ignore all directions, yet use this app on occasion to predict eta to work. Even though I never follow its directions, the eta is creepily accurate. Also, since this is user-updated, idiots often update something stupid (like "construction ahead" when it's in the median of a freeway and a seven year project that didn't close off the freeway or even a lane). **Updated 2 /17/18: directions dropped me in the middle of a road. Tried to report the map issue. Two weeks later I got a message that states they tried to contact me and I didn't respond, so they're closing the report. I can see they tried to contact me, though I wasn't alerted, and there is literally no way to respond. No help articles to explain how to reply, no way to contact anyone at all. Also it keeps putting me on toll roads when I selected not to, but directions lack info when lanes split and you should veer to one lane to not end up on a toll road.**

Author: Dee Dee Carr
Body: I don't think the Android app works near as well as the Windows app. The compass has not worked since I downloaded it on my first Android phone. I have sent multiple reports to fix it, but nothing has been done and no one has contacted me about it. Also, it has never remembered my routes to and from work and the Windows app did. The Windows app would ask me if I was going home or to work and the Android app only does once in a great while. I'm very dissappointed in the Android version.

App Name: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Laporsha Ford
Body: So the issue where the GPS would bug and not show you in the right location was fixed. Now I never updated my app because I liked it how it was. I'm so mad that I went ahead and updated it. The new update is great however it took away a feature that was one of the main reasons I even downloaded the app. Being able to choose whether you want it the faster routes or shorter roots is a major influence and why I got the app. There's a limit on distance, I can always talk to my phone to set a reminder that's actually more noticeable and louder than the unnoticeable reminder Waze gives you, so the only reason I truly kept it was because of that feature. The new update has taken that feature away and in my eyes it has become just another Google Maps but words. It's such that there is no longer a point in me having Waze when Google is just as good if not better as I'm even able to get travel history detailed. Please bring the feature back, otherwise I'm just wasting a bunch of space for a copy

Author: Jon Livingston
Body: I'm a recent convert from Google Maps. I very much like the Waze app and it's features. I have one complaint and suggestion for improvement. It would be very nice when minimizing the app to access other apps, for a pop up navigation display to be an option, like Google offers. Since Waze remains active when minimized, it shouldn't be that difficult to add an auto display at the top of the screen with your next turn by turn instruction. That works make it a 5 star app in my opinion.

App Name: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
App: Waze - GPS, Maps, Traffic Alerts & Live Navigation
Author: Rob Clarke
Body: I have had this app for some time and initially thought it was amazing. The promise of helping cut through traffic and save huge chunks of journey times seemed to good to be true. Well folks, it was. Beware. Believe what this app tells you and will click up more miles than Mo Farah in training. Let me tell you why. I leave for work and it finds me the quickest route. I check it against other routes and yup, the one it has selected for me is at least 20 minutes faster than any others. So of I go. But, less than half a mile in I veer  off course on the route I prefer. And lo and behold all of a sudden the app tells me my arrival time is actually one minute earlier. But more worryingly this route is 10 miles shorter. So why didn't it select this route to begin with? And this happens repeatedly through my journey. I take alternative turns to those suggested and my journey time never increases despite the app telling me I'll be adding minutes. The algorithms are wrong. This app makes you drive further and take longer. Don't trust it folks.

Subject: Problems now
Body: I have been using Waze for years.  The last two trips have been a much different experience.  No updates from Waze.  Map was working but traffic problems were not reported - traffic jam in Cincinnati on I75 with no notifications.  Removed and reinstalled.  That recovered real-time notifications but won’t let me log back in. All prior information, addresses have been lost. Tried to recover account for two days with no luck.  Feels like servers are offline overwhelmed or in process of being shut down.  Likely to jump to another tool.  Simply can’t keep trying when I need a working tool.

Author: Sahil The Great
Subject: Best Navigation App
Body: This is definitely the best app on any device for navigation. Beats Apple maps, beats the standard google maps (yes, I know waze is owned by google now). Love the dynamic aspect to it. Love knowing where cops are (most of the time) as well as other road hazards. I have had plenty of my friends download the app, and they've all loved it. Even those that don't like it, I make them retry it, and they re-evaluate their opinions.

Author: zerodivin3
Subject: Hate to delete this navigation app
Body: But for a long time now, probably almost 2 years (I know, I’m faithful). I’ve realized this thing eats up SO much data. I run out of 2 gigs in less than a week on long drives. I love everything about it (especially hazardous objects on road and police), but it’s missing an important feature I’ve secretly been waiting for that google maps has and that’s the whole standby screen to save battery and phone from heating up. Many times Waze redirects me from traffic which was cool, but then I realized after a couple times, I actually lost time AND gas because of it due to stops and whatnot instead of just sitting in traffic. Not that it hasn’t helped at other times, but I’ve learned that most of the time the traffic it predicts has long dissipated (so much for “live”. Overall, it’s just been getting worse and I’ve thought to delete this app a long time ago if it weren’t for the social part, but then I realized all my friends haven’t touched it in forever and I only use it to share with my wife who doesn’t even realize I send her ETAs anyways till I’m already there and she calls me to ask me if I’ve arrived lol. It’s been Waze, but ultimately, my data is more important to me than the 80% ghost police notifications and my safe speed limit travels.

Et aussi peut-être un petit bouton d'accès direct sur carte pour pouvoir alterner directement entre péage et gratuit À tout moment sans rentrer dans les menus et les sous menus. 
Voilà à part ça je ne vois rien de plus à améliorer... 😉
Translated Body: Excellent !! otherwise 2 suggestions, the possibility of having an alternating route between free route but in an optimized way by making us go through the fastest routes fluid and practical and difficult areas by the tolls. And also maybe a little button on the map to be able to directly switch between toll and free At any time without entering the menus and submenus. Author: YvainLB
Subject: Très bon compagnon de route mais...
Body:
[maj du 21/02/2018]
Le problème évoqué en novembre est toujours d’actualité... c’est très pénible de subir les approximations de localisation des dangers sur la route ou pire, de naviguer en centre ville... suis-je seul concerné ?

[ajout du 18/11/17] 
- depuis quelques jours, je constate que la carte est en retard de plusieurs dizaines de mètres ce qui altère le bon déroule du guidage.

Je suis très content de Waze que ce soit pour des trajets en France comme à l'étranger. 
Quelques points sont à améliorer malgré tout :
- le passage en mode nuit ne fonctionne plus correctement de manière automatique.
- malheureusement, il n'est plus possible de signaler des événements dans le sens de circulation inverse.
- il serait intéressant de pouvoir programmer un trajet avec plus d'une étape intermédiaire.
Translated Body: [maj 21/02/2018] The problem mentioned in November is still relevant ... it is very painful to undergo approximations of location of the dangers on the road or worse, to navigate in the city center ... I only concerned? [added 18/11/17] - for a few days, I see that the map is delayed several tens of meters which impairs the smooth progress of the guidance. I am very happy with Waze whether it is for trips in France or abroad. Some points are to improve anyway: - the switch to night mode does not work properly automatically. - unfortunately, it is no longer possible to report events in the reverse direction. - it would be interesting to be able to program a trip with more than one intermediate step.

Author: Bb2132
Subject: Great app
Body:
I gave this 4 stars only because of how many times you have to press something to report it. I quick button or favorite would be great. Example: I live in a very rural area. I use this to mark deer on the roads for my coworkers that are behind me. I have to press 5 buttons in order to mark them. It's a dark and winding road with lots of deer so this is dangerous or it takes a while for me to get it marked. A quick button on the map screen for animals on the road would be fantastic. When I see a deer, I can just press that button and boom, it's done. Of course this could be a customization for people and maybe have a couple spots for quick buttons. That's just one that I use very often (10 to 15 times in 25 miles). I know others have their most frequent buttons they use. Two or three buttons across the bottom or left side would not hurt anything. You can even make them smaller like the size of the compass.

P.S. if points are not accumulating, write a review and they will appear. I’ve done that twice. lol

Author: Vatomatic
Subject: Now useless for EV driver
Body:
Electric vehicle (EV) often seek the shortest route between points at the expense of time since charging stations are not always available along the way. The removal of the SHORTEST/FASTEST route option in the last update turned this app into "just another navigation app" for EV drivers. 
I am removing it from my phone now.

Author: App turned to crap
Subject: What happened Waze!
Body: Waze was the best GPS app out there and it has grown tremendously through word of mouth uses who advocate for the app. Now, my friend and I can be in the same car, with the same settings (fastest route, tolls ok, etc.) and it gives us different routes.... how? Often GPS can’t be found, you can no longer report hidden cops on the “other side” and the app constantly adjusts. Today I was going North and the GPS kept re-routing and thought I was going South. I reset my phone and checked other GPS apps, the problem is not on my end.... can we fix this ASAP? I’d hate to stop using all together but the reliability has gone down hill!!!

Subject: Almost perfect
Body:
I drive full time for Uber and Lyft and rely on Waze to get me around Boston, having recently moved here. 
Overall I’m happy with most of the routes it takes. Learning some of the area now, I know it has taken me on a few unnecessarily long trips, but those aren’t a regular occurrence. 
Also I’m confused by the “Scoreboard.” It syncs to Facebook, but doesn’t show all my friends at times and other times it does. Also, is a “point” a mile driven? 
Ultimately it’s not about that, but if it’s offered, it should work right? :) 
Also, in Mass, I don’t need to know about every pothole on the Turnpike. The thing never stops saying “Pothole on Road Ahead.” I realize this is a double edged sword, so I will digress.

Author: Jackjascdafcad
Subject: Suggestions please read. Thanks!!
Body:
Best app ever; however, I think it could be even greater if the following suggestions were made. Thank you!

1). The app simply says, for example, "in one mile turn right". Why doesn't it say "in one mile turn right on (insert street name & number) so the driver doesn't have to take his/her eyes off the road to look down to know which street to turn onto. 

2). When you arrive at your destination it would be nice if it included the address, for example "you have arrived at 123 Sesame Street", not "your destination", so again the driver doesn't have to take eyes off the road to confirm address. To that point it should also include the address & not simply "home" "work" or whatever location was searched (McDonald's, Starbuck's) in the direction list, in case the driver does not see the location or needs additional confirmation. This prevents the driver from having to re-search the address.

Body:
Ahora no calcula bien el tiempo, las rutas que indica ya no son las más rápidas y en ocasiones marca qué hay tráfico por una ruta en la que no lo hay, hace dar vueltas innecesarias con mucha regularidad.
Antes la indicación estaba relacionada con los letreros en las desviaciones ahora marca el nombre de la calle y por lo regular uno no sabe los nombres de las calles, por eso usamos un gps. 
Recuerdo que también uno decidía si ir por la ruta más rápida o la más corta.
A pesar de todo lo anterior de lo qué hay disponible es la mejor, se que mejorarán y serán nuevamente esa aplicación que yo amaba
Translated Subject: Very good at the beginning, but they are getting worse
Translated Body: Now it does not calculate the time well, the routes indicated are no longer the fastest and sometimes mark what is traffic on a route where there is not, makes unnecessary turns very regularly. Before the indication was related to the signs in the deviations now it marks the name of the street and usually one does not know the names of the streets, for that reason we used a gps. I remember that one also decided whether to go by the fastest route or the shortest one. Despite all the above of what is available is the best, I know that they will improve and they will be again that application that I loved

Author: Bb2132
Subject: Great app
Body:
I gave this 4 stars only because of how many times you have to press something to report it. I quick button or favorite would be great. Example: I live in a very rural area. I use this to mark deer on the roads for my coworkers that are behind me. I have to press 5 buttons in order to mark them. It's a dark and winding road with lots of deer so this is dangerous or it takes a while for me to get it marked. A quick button on the map screen for animals on the road would be fantastic. When I see a deer, I can just press that button and boom, it's done. Of course this could be a customization for people and maybe have a couple spots for quick buttons. That's just one that I use very often (10 to 15 times in 25 miles). I know others have their most frequent buttons they use. Two or three buttons across the bottom or left side would not hurt anything. You can even make them smaller like the size of the compass.

2/20/18 points are not accumulating again. The other problems have not been addressed either. App can be very unsafe to use at times

Subject: App has huge problems
Body:

Usually it just gives up trying to figure out which way to connect and uses default speaker on the phone which I can’t hear. 

Is would super helpful if it worked with Apple car play so the map would actually appear on the large screen on my dash!

I wear hearing aids that are Bluetooth connect to my phone.  The app almost always automatically connect to my hearing aids.  That in itself isn’t a problem. BUT it makes my hearing aids go on full volume and drives me absolutely bat s**t crazy!  

Sadly, even though it much prefer Waze over any other map available...  I seldom use it due to its lack of functionality in my Ford and its propensity to connect to by hearing aids -vs- the truck. 

I welcome feedback from developers if they care at all.  Even willing to help out with hearing aid info etc.

Author: love your waze!
Subject: Waze love!!! ♥️♥️♥️
Body:
Waze is the best!  I dislike following the long or slow way around when I can beat traffic and learn new and different approaches to getting to my destinations. I get to see a change in scenery and have even found a few off the beaten trail places to eat and shop. Even though I’ve lived in this area I found a new way to get to one of my most frequented stops. I was taking what looked to be the straightest and fasted way but much to my surprise taking 2 more turns eliminated the traffic lights and congestion. I use Waze even on short trips as it is great to keep your friends posted as to your ETA. Making travel more simple.  The only complaint that I can think of is that it does sometimes send you through seedy areas. Is there a way to either warn you or give you the choice to eliminate those areas, maybe a character to submit a “creep”report or some type of high crime area report? Food for thought?  
Many thanxx to Waze!

Author: Benefitted
Subject: Inaccurate navigation
Body:
I have been using TomTom and due to its lack of Places of interest and inbuilt search engine I decided to give Waze a go used it for a few months and I have to say the turn by turn instructions are inaccurate I went to a destination which I knew and tested this out on both journeys it took me on a wild goose chase added additional miles to the journey and got me stuck in slow moving traffic. 
On several occasions is showed traffic further ahead but I decided to ignore its instructions and went ahead to find the road completely clear. 
It also has annoying and intrusive ads popping up at the junctions which diverts your attention from the road if you’re an occasional user I suppose it’s fine but for someone using it on daily basis it’s a No No. I don’t understand how waze expects drivers to update the info like hazards and traffic on the go especially when it’s illegal to touch your phone or use it whilst driving in the uk. Navigation wise I personally experienced TomTom to be far mor accurate with route and traffic information I wouldn’t use waze again and wouldn’t recommend it to anyone else either !!!

Author: m-Aurelius
Subject: Be a road ninja
Body:
With Waze, you always feel like you're a step ahead of all the other drivers around you. That speed trap that everyone is suddenly braking for? You knew about it 2 miles earlier. The stalled car on the side of the road  sitting precariously close to the right lane? You already got over because you knew it was coming.

I always feel like I'm highly aware of everything going around me on the road while using Waze. There are rarely surprises...and if there is something new, I get the satisfaction of reporting it and getting "thanked" by other Wazers. So satisfying. This is crowdsourcing at its finest. If you've never given Waze a shot, try it now. Give it a week and I promise you'll never look back.

Donc impossible de se faire une idée précise de la circulation. Pour signaler un danger il faut passer par trop d’écrans successifs.  C’est pas pratique voir dangereux. Bref gratuit oui mais se dégrade au fur et à mesure du trou a l’inverse des pubs envahissantes.
Translated Body: Waze becomes slower than before and less accurate. At a crossroads you have to wait for Waze to know where you are. Updates after a plug are not refreshed enough. 40 minutes after the last report it is always indicated a slowdown while the traffic has become fluid again. So impossible to get a clear idea of ​​the traffic. To signal a danger you have to go through too many screens. It's not practical to see dangerous. In short, free of charge, but it deteriorates as the hole is reversed invasive ads.

O sistema de pontos do placar apresenta muita falha. Vc cumpre com as metas mas os pontos não são creditados. Fiz uma viagem de 1900 Km, mas não recebi a pontuação por ter batido a meta de dirigir mais de 805 Km em uma semana. Entrei em contato com o suporte do app, mas eles não fizeram nenhuma questão de investigar o ocorrido.
Translated Body: Application tosses you into every mouthful that even God doubts. If you are on a long trip and the signal falls in the middle of the road, the app loses the route but it is already traced. The scoreboard system is very flawed. You meet the goals but the points are not credited. I made a trip of 1900 km, but I did not receive the score for having hit the target of driving more than 805 km in a week. I contacted app support, but they did not ask me to investigate what happened.

Author: GMoneyRob
Subject: Sound control is an issue
Body:
2 issues with sound: 
1.  Volume control is difficult.  What I think I’ve figured out is you can only control the voice volume when the voice is actually talking, otherwise you’re controlling the phone ringer volume.  If I want to control something outside the app, I should do so by hitting the home button to minimize the app first, otherwise I should be controlling the app volume.
2.  Bluetooth Linkage to car is infuriating.  No matter how many times I change the “listening on” field from my car to phone speaker, it still projects through the car.  My best guess is it’s a timing issue like above (can only change while the app is actually talking), which I think is dangerous while you’re driving to have to put so much focus on this simple task.
This didn’t use to happen.  Something has changed in an update.

Author: James Werner
Subject: Not just another GPS app.
Body:
This app is 5/5. I honestly believe it makes me a safer driver, giving fair warning about traffic conditions and other things such as hazards on the road and police.

I really like the intuitive rerouting when it detects traffic problems. I use it every day on my 1 hour commute and it varies my route regularly based on traffic conditions (but not so much that you don’t know where you are).

If you drive a lot this app is an absolute must. It’s not just a regular GPS app by any measure.

Author: Deuce0nenik
Subject: Review
Body: I use google map gps instead. The only reason I do not like to use Waze is just to many buttons. Just try to make it a little more simplified. But the main reason I do not use Waze is and I hope Waze is reading this. I prefer google over Waze because as I’m driving and I know that Waze uses real time traffic and directs you into the quickest route. But the problem is, as I said, too many buttons. As I’m driving, I would like to see what other routes are available on screen and click on it like with google. With Waze, I have to tap a button, tap route and then go from there. Why not just put it on screen so we can see and choose for ourselves rather have to go off the screen and tap onto other buttons. With google, I see it on screen, I don’t like a route I’m currently on, I just tap on another route and it tells you whether it’s the same eta or not or maybe an extra .2 miles but maybe a quicker route. If I can see different routes while on the Waze map while I’m driving and can tap on it to change my route, I’d have no problem using Waze.
